# PLIG-6922 – Mobile Access for CPM and LCO Home Page

## Technical Analysis & Limitation

### Requirement

The story requires CPM and LCO users to see the following three Opportunity sections at the top of the Salesforce Mobile Home page:

* Current Loan – OnePATHE Opportunities
* Upcoming Loan – OnePATHE Opportunities
* Past Due Loan – OnePATHE Opportunities

These sections should display the same opportunities currently available on the CRM 360 desktop Home Page.

### Current Implementation

The existing desktop Home Page implementation uses custom Screen Flows to display:

* Current Loan Opportunities
* Upcoming Loan Opportunities
* Past Due Loan Opportunities

This solution works correctly on the desktop Home Page.

### Technical Limitation

After reviewing Salesforce Mobile Home capabilities, I found that Salesforce Mobile Home supports only standard card types such as:

* Pinned Reports
* Recent
* My Calendar
* Salesforce Events
* Tasks
* Favorites
* Pinned Lists

Salesforce Mobile Home does not support adding custom Screen Flow components directly as Mobile Home cards.

Because of this platform limitation, the current desktop Screen Flow solution cannot be replicated on the Mobile Home page using standard Salesforce configuration.

### Possible Approaches

#### Option 1 – Standard Salesforce Approach

* Create separate reports for:

  * Current Loan Opportunities
  * Upcoming Loan Opportunities
  * Past Due Loan Opportunities
* Make the reports available to CPM and LCO users.
* Configure or pin these reports for mobile access where supported.

Pros:

* Uses standard Salesforce functionality.
* Lower development effort.
* Easier maintenance.

Cons:

* User experience differs from the desktop Home Page.
* May require user interaction to access reports.

#### Option 2 – Custom Development Approach

* Design and develop a custom mobile solution to display the opportunity sections within the Salesforce mobile experience.

Pros:

* Closer to the desktop experience.
* More automated user experience.

Cons:

* Additional development effort.
* Requires further design and technical evaluation.

### Recommendation

Before starting development, I recommend discussing this Salesforce Mobile limitation and confirming the preferred approach with the business team to ensure the solution aligns with expectations.



